HEADWORD: Protocanonical
<hw>Pro`to*ca*non"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or
pertaining to the first canon, or that which contains the authorized
collection of the books of Scripture; -- opposed to
<contr>deutero-canonical</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Protocatechuic</ent>⟦br⟧
